# Movie Recommender System

## Description
This project is a C++ Movie Recommender System that provides personalized movie
 recommendations based on user preferences. It reads user and movie data to
  suggest movies that align with individual user tastes.

## Features
- Loads user data and preferences
- Reads movie information
- Recommends movies based on user preferences
- Efficient recommendation algorithm

## Files
- `RSUser.cpp` / `RSUser.h`: Handles user data and preferences.
- `RSUsersLoader.cpp` / `RSUsersLoader.h`: Loads and processes user data.
- `Movie.cpp` / `Movie.h`: Manages movie information and attributes.
- `RecommenderSystem.cpp` / `RecommenderSystem.h`: Core recommendation logic.
- `RecommenderSystemLoader.cpp` / `RecommenderSystemLoader.h`: Loads and
 initializes the recommender system.

## Installation
1. Clone the repository.
    ```bash
    git clone <repository-url>
    ```
2. Navigate to the project directory.
    ```bash
    cd movie-recommender-system
    ```
3. Compile the source code.
    ```bash
    g++ -o recommender RSUser.cpp RSUsersLoader.cpp Movie.cpp
     RecommenderSystem.cpp RecommenderSystemLoader.cpp
    ```

## Usage
1. Run the compiled executable.
    ```bash
    ./recommender
    ```
2. Follow the prompts to input user preferences and receive movie recommendations.

